news.title: Bulandshahr: Demolition fears for 400 families in illegal colonies
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) recently seized Goyal's 58 properties estimated to be worth Rs 27 crore. The colony is one of several illegal developments allegedly done by Goyal and his associates over the past decade.

news.title: China's Country Garden says over 30 projects have local government support
news.para: China's largest private property developer said in a statement to Reuters that its projects were included on the so-called "white lists" of the provinces of Heinan, Hubei, Sichuan, Shandong and the municipality Chongqing.

news.title: Brihanmumbai civic body will monetise its properties: Municipal commissioner
news.para: The corporation will appoint a “world renowned real estate consultant” to prepare a masterplan for its leasehold and tenanted properties spread across the city.

news.title: Six farmhouses, boundary walls built on Aravali land demolished
news.para: The move comes after the directions of National Green Tribunal (NGT) to demolish illegal structures in areas that fall under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Protection Act (PLPA).

news.title: Vadodara: Himmatnagar housing scheme protesters detained, freed
news.para: Earlier, the residents had been issued notices in 2019, 2021 and twice last year. While many have vacated their houses, others are still staying there.

news.title: Property tax mopup lags as 2023-24 bills still to be issued in Mumbai
news.para: Till Jan 3, its collection stood at a mere Rs 606 crore. BMC is still to issue bills for property tax for the current financial year. Following govt directives, it has waived off property tax for units up to 500 square feet.

news.title: Kerala-RERA team inspects unregistered projects
news.para: The authority inspected the two plots of the development projects located in Anad and Nanniyode panchayat. These plots are being developed and sold without registering with the authority.

news.title: Affidavit relief for homeowners in merged areas of Pune
news.para: These forms are necessary to receive 40% property tax benefits offered by Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) for self-occupied properties.

news.title: MMRDA seeks Rs 4,000 crore to redevelop Mumbai's Ramabai Nagar
news.para: MMRDA has already prepared the 'detailed project report'. Terms and conditions for the loan will be publicised by MMRDA on February 5 and repayment period is likely to be 15 years.

news.title: Having house constructed in Ludhiana? Get online building plan approval
news.para: ​Once submitted, the plan will deemed to have been approved if the official responsible for approving the plan does not raise an objection in 10 days.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance's net profit up by 18% to Rs 62.28 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Disbursements made during the quarter under review went up by 27 per cent to Rs 1,252 crore, as compared to Rs 986 crore registered in the year ago period.

news.title: Conduct survey to identify illegal constructions: Bombay HC to NMMC
news.para: “While conducting the survey, information shall also be collected by the Municipal Corporation as to how many such illegal / irregular constructions have been raised after 31st December 2015,” said Chief Justice Devendra Kumar Upadhyaya and Justice Arif Doctor in Wednesday’s order.

news.title: Stilt parking must for all Ghaziabad buildings now
news.para: As per the new amendments, the provision of stilt parking will apply to all types of houses. It will not be accounted for in the calculation of the purchasable floor area ratio (FAR) but counted as part of the building’s height.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP mulls action on officials for failure to recover property tax dues
news.para: According to BBMP sources, Munish Moudgil, special commissioner for revenue, submitted a report to the civic body’s chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath on Jan 30, recommending disciplinary action against revenue officials who have failed to recover property tax from top defaulters in the Bommanahalli zone.

news.title: Renewal of sanctioned drawings for housing projects not required: HP RERA chief
news.para: Earlier, the time limit for constructing such projects was three years which was extended to five years after which the drawings had to be renewed, a statement issued here said.

news.title: Signature Global posts Rs 2.17 crore net profit in Q3 FY24
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 301.75 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal from Rs 191.78 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals over 22,000 properties for tax default
news.para: The highest number of sealed properties, 5,441, are in the areas falling under the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation’s east zone.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP mulls action on officials for failure to recover property tax dues
news.para: According to BBMP sources, Munish Moudgil, special commissioner for revenue, submitted a report to the civic body’s chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath on Jan 30, recommending disciplinary action against revenue officials who have failed to recover property tax from top defaulters in the Bommanahalli zone.

news.title: Over 84,000 apply for regularization under Gunthewari Act
news.para: NMRDA comprises Hingna, Mouda, Kamptee, Nagpur rural, Parsheoni and some villages of Kuhi, Umred, Kalmeshwar and Saoner, A senior NMRDA official said the deadline for submission of online applications ended on January 31. An appeal was made to those who submitted online applications to give their documents in person at the divisional office.

news.title: PMAY beneficiaries in Raipur protest, accuse RMC of 'cheating'
news.para: The residents — Ghanshyam Sahu, Sattu Panka, and housing society president Suraj Yadav — told TOI that most of the PMAY beneficiaries have been allotted old flats with no window panels, doors or proper sanitation facilities.
